						<p><hi rend="bold">c. 10th Century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Beginning mutilated. Seems to make provision for offerings for a festival on the dvādasi days in the month of Mārkaḻi. The donor was a local brāhmaṇa called Pāratāyaṉ Duvēdi Nārāyaṇaṉ Gōvindan.</p>						

